** Your Title: ** Senior Software Consultant 

** Location: ** Australia - Remote or New Zealand - Remote 

** Our Division: ** Trimble Viewpoint 

** Are you interested in identifying and delivering disruptive cutting-edge technologies? **

We are searching for a seasoned Software Consultant to be a client advocate
and bridge the gap between Sales and Development.

** What You Will Do **

Join our high performing team where you will serve as an important primary
consulting liaison between the company and the customer, and will be
responsible for carrying out consulting engagements for customer accounts
using Trimble Viewpoint construction accounting and project management
software, as well as other point solutions. You will work on multiple software
consulting projects as assigned, focusing on implementation and the continued
analysis of the customer, business goals, objectives and needs.

  * Implement and assist clients with the use of of Viewpoint software core Construction ERP Jobpac Connect 
  * Analyse customers & business requirements and objectives. 
  * Provide various levels of Consultation with the clients to implement best practices, standard methodologies and desired business outcomes according to the client needs. 
  * Provide software application training services. 
  * Monitor, track, and document customer consulting calls and related activities in the Viewpoint ERP system. 

** What Skills And Experience You Should Bring **

In addition to normal business Core Competencies, you will have:

  * Strong working knowledge of Jobpac Connect ERP, Spectrum or Vista 
  * Ability to write Business Specifications for ERP modifications. 
  * Several years of experience either Implementing or as an Administrator/Lead user of Jobpac Connect ERP. 
  * A University degree in business, accounting, or IT, or payroll administration, or equivalent work experience. 
  * Several years of experience as a business consultant. 
  * Software implementation project work experience, focusing on external client relations. 
  * Be a subject matter expertise in one or both of the following areas: Accounting principles and practices (e.g. payroll, accounts payable, accounts receivable, inventory, purchase orders, general ledger), and/or Construction project management principles and practices (e.g. project set-up via estimate, project buy-out, project documents, project change orders, job costing, job billing). 
  * Be able to travel local and nationally as required (up to 50%) but frequency can be managed by Senior Software Consultant but typically a kick off and planning and a further visit to customer site at implementation stage. 
  * You should possess a valid driver’s license. 

